title: Accessibility
description:
The white curb areas are ADA accessible on both the Departure (upper) and Arrival (lower) Levels. Please do not leave your car unattended at the curbside.

Extra wide accessible parking spaces are conveniently located in all parking facilities at the Airport. Please note that at this time, Terminal parking is accessible from the Departure (upper) Level only.

All restrooms are wheelchair accessible.

More information about accessibility

title: Parking
description:
Terminal Parking A1

Terminal Parking Rate:
$2 per hour up to $20 per 24-hour period

The terminal parking facilities have covered and uncovered parking spaces adjacent to or in close vicinity of the terminal. For those dropping off or picking up passengers, A1, B2 and C offer a limited amount of economical 2-hour parking spaces on the lower level near the entrance to the terminal.

More information about parking

title: Parking
description:
Main Street Off-Airport Parking

Main Street Parking Rate:
$2 per hour up to $14 per 24-hour period

The most economical option, the uncovered Main Street Parking is located at 1512 Main Street in Irvine. Courtesy shuttle service to and from the Riley Terminal is available every 15 minutes. Shuttle buses are lift-equipped. Main Street Lot shuttle pick-up locations at the Terminal are on the Arrival (lower) Level at the third island of the Ground Transportation Center for Terminals A and B, and in front of Terminal C Arrival (lower) Level just north of the crosswalk into Parking Structure B2.

title: Rail
description:
iShuttle Route A connects to the Tustin Metrolink train station, where trains run down to Oceanside in San Diego County, up to Los Angeles, or to San Bernardino. The iShuttle stops on the Arrival (lower) Level, curbside, in front of Terminal B.

More information about Metrolink Trains

More information on iShuttle

title: Rental Cars
description:
Ground Transportation Center
On-site rental car companies offer convenient services at the Terminal. Their rental car counters are located on the Arrival (lower) Level, between Terminals A and B, right across from the statue of John Wayne.
More information about on-site and off-site rental car agencies

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description:
Ground Transportation Center

Taxis
John Wayne Airport Yellow Cab offers convenient taxicab service to travelers from the Ground Transportation Center (GTC) on the Arrival (lower) Level between Terminals A and B.
Fares (subject to change):
$3.50 for the flag drop and first 1/5 mile
$0.55 for each 1/5 mile, after the first 1/5 mile ($2.75 per mile)
$32.00 per hour wait time (Approximately $0.53 per minute)

Disneyland Resort Express
The Disneyland Resort Express bus stop is located on the Arrival (lower) Level in the Ground Transportation Center. Airport shuttle service operates hourly 7 days a week.
Visit this website or call (800) 828-6699 for more information.

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description:
Local Bus Service
Orange County Transportation Authority (OCTA) buses, Routes 76 and 212, and the iShuttle, Route A, stop on the Arrival (lower) Level, curbside, in front of Terminal B.

More information on OCTA buses

More information on iShuttle

title: Wi-Fi
description: John Wayne Airport is pleased to provide free wireless internet access to passengers throughout the concourses, lounges and concession areas of JWA's Thomas F. Riley Terminal. Passengers wishing to access the free service should look for JWAFREEWIFI in their device's available wireless networks list.
